<div class="founder-page">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-text">
        <p class="eyebrow">Meet the Founder</p>
        <h1>Pete Olander</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Founder &amp; CEO of Happie Beverages — building a premium functional beverage brand from the ground up, without institutional capital.</p>
        <div class="stats">
          <div class="stat"><div class="num">7</div><div class="label">Years in Beverage</div></div>
          <div class="stat"><div class="num">6</div><div class="label">States Distributed</div></div>
          <div class="stat"><div class="num">80K</div><div class="label">Retail Store Network</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-portrait">
        <img src="{{ 'pete-olander-portrait.jpg' | asset_url }}" alt="Pete Olander, Founder &amp; CEO of Happie Beverages" width="800" height="1000" loading="eager">
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="block">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">The Origin</p>
      <h2>From J.P. Morgan to <em>plant-based</em> beverage.</h2>
      <div class="body-copy">
        <p>I came from finance — J.P. Morgan and First Western Trust — but when I decided to build a beverage brand, I knew I didn't want to do it the way most people in this space do. I didn't want to slap a label on a white-label product and call it a brand. I wanted to actually understand the plant, the community, and the science behind it — and build something rooted in trust and transparency.</p>
        <p>So I moved to California. I spent years immersed in the compliant cannabis market — working in cultivation, distribution, and learning what retail customers actually wanted. I got to understand the trends firsthand, the supply chain from seed to shelf, and the people who had been building this industry long before it was mainstream. That experience made Happie a true California-rooted company, not just in name but in DNA.</p>
        <p>That foundation is what sets Happie apart. The company runs two product lines at the intersection of the two fastest-growing beverage categories in the country: hemp-derived Delta-9 THC beverages as a premium alcohol alternative, and Fungi Fusion — a line of adaptogenic mushroom drinks formulated with clinical-dose Lion's Mane, Cordyceps, and Reishi. Every batch is third-party tested. COAs are available to customers. Transparency isn't a marketing line for us — it's the reason the company exists.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="block alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">What I've Built</p>
      <h2>Seven years of beverage development. <em>Bootstrapped.</em></h2>
      <p class="lede">Career milestones across finance, formulation, manufacturing, and distribution — built without a single round of institutional funding.</p>
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="when">Finance Career</div>
          <h3>J.P. Morgan · First Western Trust · SAP Implementations</h3>
          <p>Built expertise in deal structure, capital markets, systems, and high-net-worth client management before transitioning to CPG.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="when">2019 — Founding</div>
          <h3>Happie Beverages, Inc. — Delaware C-Corp</h3>
          <p>Founded the company on a thesis: premium ingredients, real dosing, no medical-claim shortcuts. Wellness with an edge.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="when">2024 — THC Relaunch</div>
          <h3>Hemp-derived Delta-9 line — 5mg + 10mg sparkling</h3>
          <p>Reformulated and relaunched the THC line aligned with the federal/state 10mg cap. Dual-dose strategy designed for state variance.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="when">2025 — Fungi Fusion</div>
          <h3>Clinical-dose mushroom beverage line</h3>
          <p>Launched Lion's Mane (900mg), Cordyceps (700mg), and Reishi (400mg) drinks — dual-extracted for 3–7x bioavailability, with ocean-derived Aquamin minerals.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="when">2026 — Scale</div>
          <h3>National distribution &amp; AI-integrated operations</h3>
          <p>National distribution contract covering an 80,000-store retail network through a 7-year co-pack partnership. AI operations stack across competitive intelligence, sales, content, and distribution.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="block">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">The Brand</p>
      <h2>Two product lines. <em>One conviction.</em></h2>
      <p class="lede">Happie operates at the intersection of the two fastest-growing beverage categories in the country — built for the people redefining what wellness looks like.</p>
      <div class="pillars">
        <div class="pillar">
          <span class="pillar-tag">Drink Happie</span>
          <h3>The premium alcohol alternative.</h3>
          <p>Sparkling Delta-9 THC + CBD beverages. Federally compliant, third-party tested, 30 calories. Same ritual. Better ingredients. Designed for adults rethinking their relationship with alcohol.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar">
          <span class="pillar-tag">Fungi Fusion</span>
          <h3>The clinical-dose mushroom drink.</h3>
          <p>Caffeine-free functional beverage with dual-extracted Lion's Mane, Cordyceps, and Reishi. Built around clarity, recovery, and balance — supported by ocean minerals, not sugar.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="block alt">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">In the Press</p>
      <h2>Featured coverage of Pete &amp; Happie.</h2>
      <div class="press-grid">
        <a class="press-card" href="https://medium.com/authority-magazine/peter-olander-of-happie-5-things-i-wish-someone-told-me-before-i-became-a-founder-059218f2dca1" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <div class="press-outlet">Authority Magazine</div>
          <h3>5 Things I Wish Someone Told Me Before I Became A Founder</h3>
          <p>A long-form interview on finance, grit, building Happie, and what emerging-industry founders should know before they start.</p>
          <span class="read-more">Read on Authority Magazine</span>
        </a>
        <a class="press-card" href="https://www.ibtimes.com/inside-rise-drink-happie-pete-olanders-plant-based-approach-modern-well-being-3791533" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <div class="press-outlet">International Business Times</div>
          <h3>Inside The Rise Of Drink Happie</h3>
          <p>Pete Olander's plant-based approach to modern well-being and how Happie is positioning at the intersection of wellness and category-defining beverage innovation.</p>
          <span class="read-more">Read on IBTimes</span>
        </a>
        <a class="press-card" href="https://open.spotify.com/episode/6iSFQSceOzoJlFHvIjModC" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <div class="press-outlet">The Kara Goldin Show</div>
          <h3>Founder Spotlight — Pete Olander &amp; the Happie story.</h3>
          <p>Pete joins Hint founder Kara Goldin to share the journey from finance to founding a hemp-derived THC and functional mushroom beverage brand.</p>
          <span class="read-more">Listen to the episode</span>
        </a>
        <a class="press-card" href="https://natlawreview.com/press-releases/happie-beverages-expands-national-presence-plant-based-innovation" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          <div class="press-outlet">USA Today Network / National Law Review</div>
          <h3>Happie Beverages Expands National Presence with Plant-Based Innovation</h3>
          <p>Wire feature distributed April 3, 2026 across 150+ regional papers via EINPresswire — covering Happie's national distribution scale-up and dual-line strategy.</p>
          <span class="read-more">Read the feature</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="block philosophy">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">What I Believe</p>
      <h2>Build the machine before <em>the moment arrives.</em></h2>
      <div class="body-copy">
        <p>You don't need permission to build something real. The playbook that says you need a co-founder, a seed round, and a 20-person team before you can compete is outdated. What you need is discipline, the right infrastructure, and the conviction to keep building when the timeline doesn't match your ambition.</p>
        <p class="pull">"Every challenge I've faced — regulatory complexity, capital constraints, partnership failures — taught me something that made the business stronger."</p>
        <p>The regulatory headwinds that felt like punishment forced me to build compliance systems that became a barrier to entry for competitors. The capital constraints forced operational efficiency that venture-backed brands can't replicate. The AI operations stack wasn't a luxury — it was a survival mechanism that became a competitive advantage.</p>
        <p>When the window opens — and it always does — you want to be the one who's ready, not the one scrambling to catch up. That's the founder I'm trying to be. That's the company I'm trying to build.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="connect">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Connect</p>
      <h2>Find Pete <em>here.</em></h2>
      <p class="lede">For press, partnership, distribution, or collaboration inquiries.</p>
      <div class="connect-links">
        <a class="primary" href="mailto:pete@livehappie.com">Email Pete</a>
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/pete-olander-580a657/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
        <a href="https://www.drinkhappie.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">drinkhappie.com</a>
        <a href="https://www.instagram.com/happiefusion/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">@happiefusion</a>
        <a href="https://x.com/HappieBeverage" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">@HappieBeverage</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</div>

